&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your experience includes…&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD in Analytical Chemistry or related discipline e.g., Biochemistry, Biotechnology or Pharmaceutical Science, with 0-3 years of industry experience in biotech, pharmaceutical, and/or CROs. Postdoc experience is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on Experience in LC-MS based bioanalysis of proteins, oligos or small molecules in biological matrix is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth scientific knowledge and hands on technical expertise on LC-MS, LC-MS/MS, and chromatography methodologies and instrumentation is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency of using Sciex Triple Quadrupole LC-MS/MS system or Thermo Orbitrap mass spectrometers such as Q Exactive series or Exploris series.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with lab automation technologies is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are interested in…&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, optimize, and validate bioanalytical methods to measure proteins, oligos, and lipids in biological samples, including cells, biofluids, and tissues, to support the development of discovery, preclinical and clinical programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute experiments from sample preparation, LC-MS/MS operation to data analysis &amp;amp; interpretation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide CROs for method transfer CROs and serve as technical expert for method trouble shooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write internal assay protocols, ROPs, qualification plans, and sample analysis reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide maintenance, quality control and troubleshooting of LC-MS systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated bioanalytical scientist to fulfil a Scientist role in our DMPK group. The candidate will be responsible for developing and employing LC-MS methods to characterize and quantitate proteins, oligos and lipid in cells, blood and tissues to support discovery, preclinical, and clinical programs for a variety of therapeutic indications. The ideal candidate must have excellent communication skills and is willing to work in a highly dynamic and fast-paced work&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tessera employees are creative and collaborative problem solvers. They have a strong sense of integrity and unwavering commitment to scientific excellence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
