&lt;p&gt;Dr. Gang Sun has over 17 years of experience in DMPK and Bioanalyticals. Dr. Sun has worked with diverse drug modalities, including small molecules, proteins, oligos, and mRNA, across various therapeutic areas such as oncology, immunology, and gene editing. Dr. Sun has actively contributed to the support of discovery, preclinical, and clinical programs. He currently leads a multidisciplinary team at Tessera Therapeutics, where he oversees DMPK, bioanalytical, clinical pharmacology, biomarker, and ADA support for the development of Gene Writing and Rewriting Therapeutics. Prior to joining Tessera Therapeutics, Dr. Sun held positions at Translate Bio, Corbus Pharmaceuticals, Merrimack Pharmaceuticals, Merck &amp;amp; Co., and Covance. His academic credentials include a Ph.D. in Chemistry from Peking University, an M.S. from Qingdao University of Science and Technology, and a B.S. from Qingdao University.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
